<p>I want to navigate to another page without reloading the controller:</p>  <pre><code>  .state('app.viewcomments', {     url: '/viewcomments/?new',     views: {       'menuContent': {         templateUrl: 'templates/posts/view-comment.html',         controller: 'SearchController'       }     }   })   </code></pre>  <p>What i want is if I navigate to this url from anywhere it should not reload <code>SearchController</code> based on <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14974271/can-you-change-a-path-without-reloading-the-controller-in-angularjs">this solution </a> it tried :</p>  <pre><code>  &lt;a href="#/app.viewcomments/?new" class="button button-icon icon ion-plus-round"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;   &lt;a href="#app.viewcomments/?new" class="button button-icon icon ion-plus-round"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;   &lt;a href="app.viewcomments/?new" class="button button-icon icon ion-plus-round"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>but none of them worked.</p>